{"key":"processedPost-11264529","value":{"id":11264529,"first":11264412,"last":11266888,"when":1255792246,"utime":"10/17/09 06:10 PM","content":"If the light heats up the terrarium that much, you're probably using an incandescent light bulb, which is almost as bad as no light at all.&nbsp; Use fluorescent.&nbsp; That's probably also why your humidity is low.&nbsp; For a given amount of moisture in the air, a 20F temperature rise will cut the relative humidity in half.<br /><br />Air exchange is the number one pinning trigger, so you need more holes or to fan more.&nbsp; Get rid of any heating pads etc.&nbsp; If you're growing in your house, they're not necessary, and actually counterproductive.&nbsp; It's the reason you have condensation, even though your humidity is too low.<br />RR","title":"Re: Heres my problem..","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}